IGHT), and 30% (STECKMAP) for light-weighted quantities, and 20% (FADO),\n60% (STARLIGHT), and 20% (STECKMAP) for mass-weighted quantities. That implies\na severe overestimation of the mass-to-light ratio and stellar mass, even in\nthe presence of a mild contribution from the nebular continuum. Our work\nunderlines the importance of a self-consistent treatment of nebular emission,\nwhich is the only route towards a reliable determination of the assembly of any\nhigh-sSFR galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Sep 2021 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-23"}
