-R model can reproduce transport,\nacceleration, decay, and dropouts of the outer radiation belt anywhere from\nshort timescales (i.e., geomagnetic storms) and very long timescales (i.e.,\nsolar cycle) variations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Sep 2021 06:27:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Oct 2021 20:24:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-05"}
