ed learning tasks to estimate the\nusefulness of non-click results with brain signals and conventional information\n(i.e., content and context factors). Results show that it is feasible to\nutilize brain signals to improve usefulness estimation performance and\nenhancing human-computer interactions in \"Zero-click\" search scenarios.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Sep 2021 07:40:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-23"}
